# Supabase Configuration (REQUIRED)
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard at https://supabase.com
# 1. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 2. Go to Settings > API
# 3. Copy the Project URL and anon/public key below
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Google Maps API Key (OPTIONAL - for itinerary map features)
# Get this from Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# OpenWeather API Key (OPTIONAL - for real-time weather at destination)
# Get a free API key at: https://openweathermap.org/api
# 1. Sign up for a free account at https://home.openweathermap.org/users/sign_up
# 2. Generate an API key in your account dashboard
# 3. Paste the API key below
# 
# Features enabled with this API key:
# - Real-time weather display on trip overview tab
# - Detailed weather information on destination page
# - Temperature, conditions, high/low, humidity, wind speed
# - Weather data is automatically cached for 10 minutes to minimize API calls
# - Auto-refreshes every 10 minutes while viewing trip pages
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=

# Database Setup Instructions:
# =============================
# After setting up your Supabase project, you need to create the database tables:
# 
# 1. Go to your Supabase dashboard > SQL Editor
# 2. Copy and paste the contents of `supabase/schema.sql`
# 3. Run the SQL to create all tables and security policies
# 4. If updating an existing database, run migrations from `supabase/migrations/` in order
#
# Required Tables:
# - users (user profiles)
# - trips (trip information with status, dates, budget, etc.)
# - trip_members (trip memberships)
# - itinerary_days (daily itinerary entries)
# - activities (activities within itinerary days)
# - expenses (trip expenses)
# - expense_splits (how expenses are split)
# - memories (photos and videos)
#
# Authentication Setup:
# ====================
# 1. Go to Authentication > Providers in Supabase dashboard
# 2. Enable Google provider
# 3. Add OAuth credentials from Google Cloud Console
# 4. Configure redirect URLs (e.g., http://localhost:3000/auth/callback)

